Let g and f(x) be an odd characteristic and an irreducible polynomial of degree m over F-q respectively Then suppose that F(x) = x(m)f(x + x(-1)) becomes irreducible over F-q This paper shows that the con jugate zeros of F(x) with respect to F-q form a normal basis in F-q2mt if and only if those of f(x) form a normal basis in F-qm and the part of conjugates given as follows are linearly Independent over F-q
{gamma - gamma(-1) (gamma - gamma(-1))(q) (gamma - gamma(-1))(qm-1)}
where gamma is a zero of F(x) and thus a proper element in F-q2m In addition from the viewpoint of q polynomial this paper proposes an efficient method for checking whether or not the conjugate zeros of F(x) satisfy the condition
